title: HK & Shenzhen have constructive exchange on notification mechanism on incidents of food safety and public health
content_text:
p>The Health, Welfare and Food Bureau (HWFB) of the Hong Kong Special 
Administrative Region Government (HKSARG) and the Shenzhen Municipal Government 
had a constructive exchange on the notification mechanism between the two places 
on incidents of food safety and public health at a meeting today (November 16). The meeting was to follow up the consensus reached on September 5 at the Hong 
Kong/Shenzhen cooperation meeting between the Chief Secretary of HKSARG, Mr

Kong/Shenzhen cooperation meeting between the Chief Secretary of HKSARG, Mr 
Rafael Hui, and the Shenzhen Mayor, Mr Xu Zongheng, to expedite the setting up 
of a notification and communication system in respect of major food safety 
incidents in the two places. Speaking after today's meeting, a bureau spokesman said both sides had 
deliberated on the objective, workings and implementation details of the 
notification mechanism. On communication, both sides agreed to exchange information on major food recall

notification mechanism. On communication, both sides agreed to exchange information on major food recall 
actions; implementation, revision and updating of major food policies; and 
routine or individual food safety surveys of the city or region. Both sides also 
agreed that more in-depth discussions should be held on these matters at the 
earliest possible convenience. The spokesman added that both sides agreed that the General Office of the 
People's Government of Shenzhen Municipality and the HWFB would be the 
designated parties for the notification mechanism.  Hong Kong officials attending today's meeting were the Deputy Secretary for

Health, Welfare and Food, Mr Eddy Chan; the Director of Food and Environmental 
Hygiene, Mr Gregory Leung and his deputy director, Dr Mak Sin-ping; and the 
acting Assistant Director of Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation (Inspection 
and Quarantine), Dr Thomas Sit. Representing the Shenzhen Municipal Government at the meeting were the Secretary 
General of Shenzhen Municipal Government, Tang Jie; Vice Director of the 
Shenzhen Administration of Agriculture, Forestry and Fishery, Liang Junqian;

Shenzhen Administration of Agriculture, Forestry and Fishery, Liang Junqian; 
Vice Director General of the Shenzhen Entry-Exit Inspection and Quarantine 
Bureau, Lin Miao; Vice Director of Hong Kong and Macau Affairs Office of the 
Shenzhen Municipal Government, Wang Zongwei; Head of Food Division of Shenzhen 
Food and Drug Administration, Li Hong; and Vice Director of Office of Public 
Health Emergency Response of Shenzhen Health Bureau, Tian Yongzhang.
